meanings.sent1: She outkissed all her friends in the kissing contest.
meanings.sent2: He outkissed his girlfriend on their anniversary.
meanings.sent3: The little girl outkissed her teddy bear goodnight.
meanings.sent4: The sun outkissed the moon as it set behind the horizon.
meanings.sent5: The puppy outkissed its siblings to get the treat first.

meanings.definition: To have been kissed more than someone else.
meanings.sent1: She felt special when she was outkissed by the popular boy.
meanings.sent2: He was outkissed by his grandma at the family gathering.
meanings.sent3: The cat seemed surprised when it was outkissed by the dog.
meanings.sent4: The flower outkissed all the others in the garden, attracting more bees.
meanings.sent5: The birthday girl was outkissed by everyone at the party.
